# AI Job Search Cursor Adapter

This repository is a job application workspace. Use the existing `.claude/` files as the canonical workflow library, but execute them with Cursor tools and terminology.

## Command Mapping

When the user types or asks for:

- `/setup`: read and follow `.claude/commands/setup.md`.
- `/apply <url-or-text>`: read and follow `.claude/commands/apply.md`.
- `/expand`: read and follow `.claude/commands/expand.md`.
- `/reset`: read and follow `.claude/commands/reset.md`.
- `/scrape` or "find jobs": read and follow `.claude/skills/job-scraper/SKILL.md`.
- `/upskill`: read and follow `.claude/skills/upskill/SKILL.md`.

If Cursor does not treat the slash text as a native command, interpret it as an instruction to run the mapped workflow.

## Cursor Tool Substitutions

- `Read tool` means Cursor file/PDF reading.
- `Edit tool` or `Write tool` means Cursor file editing.
- `WebFetch` and `WebSearch` mean Cursor web fetch/search capabilities.
- `Agent tool` or "spawn a reviewer agent" means launch a Cursor subagent when available. If not available, run a clearly separated reviewer pass in the current chat before revising.
- `AskUserQuestion` means ask the user directly before making decisions the workflow marks as user-confirmed.

## Workflow Rules

- Keep `.claude/skills/job-application-assistant/*` as the source of truth for profile, writing style, evaluation, CV templates, cover letter templates, and interview prep.
- Always evaluate job fit before drafting application materials.
- Never fabricate skills, experience, achievements, company facts, or job postings.
- When documents mention agentic coding or AI tooling, name the tool the candidate actually used, such as Cursor or Claude Code.
- Compile and inspect generated PDFs before calling an application complete: `lualatex` for CVs and `xelatex` for cover letters.
- Keep Claude Code compatibility intact unless the user explicitly asks to remove it.
